IT is no new thing for the Spaniards to envy the felicity of the Germans; 
                     •
                  or they did it many years ago. About he year of Chriſt 1419. the King of Spain forbad the German Merchants to ſail in the Spaniſh Seas, and puniſhed ſuch of them as he took in diſobedience to that Order, he took 40 ſhips, and killed all the Merchants. Albert. Cratzius in Sax. ſuo. l. 11. c. 3.
